A vintage 1960s newspaper printing press room in Singapore, with large mechanical rollers churning out fresh broadsheets, dramatic shadows cast by hanging industrial lamps, scattered paper ballots floating through the air like confetti, an old CRT computer monitor displaying garbled static and error symbols sitting incongruously among the antique machinery, warm sepia and amber tones, dust particles visible in shafts of light, the atmosphere conveying rushed chaos and technical malfunction in an era of transition between old and new media.
